  <summary>A 1 vs. 1 fighting game</summary>
  <description>
    <p>
      Domestique Baston is a 1 vs 1 fighting game. Well. You know what that
      is... It’s intended for casual gamers as the gameplay is simple...
    </p>
    <p>
      It pictures a couple fighting each other at home. That’s the reason why
      there is only 1 background and 2 playable characters.
    </p>
    <p>
      This game is in French slang just because it’s funny. No other reason.
      Besides, who really cares about, for instance, the story or even what’s
      told in such a game?
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        Use Alt-Enter to enter/exit full screen mode.
      </li>
      <li>
        When playing with a keyboard, the LEFT player uses the E, S, R, D keys
        for buttons, and the F, C, V, B keys for moving; the RIGHT player uses
        the O, K, P, L keys for buttons, and the arrow keys for moving.
      </li>
      <li>
        We strongly recommend you <em>do not</em> play on a keyboard as there
        are "ghosting" issues (some key combinations do not work).
      </li>
    </ul>
  </description>
